# The condition and quality of being [[godly]], [[pious]], scrupulously observant of all the teaching's of one's religion, practicing virtue and avoiding sin.
#:'''1562''' ''Bishops, Priests, and Deacons are not commanded by God's laws either to vow the estate of single life or to abstain from marriage. Therefore it is lawful also for them, as for all other Christian men, to marry at their own discretion, as they shall judge the same to serve better to '''godliness'''.'' — ''The Thirty-Nine Articles'', [[s:Thirty-Nine Articles|Point 32]].
#:'''1604''' ''Nay, but he prated, 
#:''And spoke such scurvy and provoking terms 
#:''Against your honour 
#:''That, with the little '''godliness''' I have, 
#:''I did full hard forbear him. — Shakespeare, ''Othello'', [[s:The_Tragedy_of_Othello,_The_Moor_of_Venice#ACT_1._SCENE_II._Another_street.|Act 1, Scene 2]]

